      },
      {
        "legenda": "The global wealth map is being redrawn. For decades, capital followed a familiar route - New York, London, the usual financial hubs. That's no longer the whole story.\nSmaller jurisdictions like St Kitts & Nevis, Panama, and São Tomé & Príncipe are becoming integral parts of sophisticated wealth strategies as complementary layers that add flexibility, tax efficiency, and growth potential.\nThe 2026 GAAR Report makes it clear: smaller countries are outperforming larger ones on governance, risk management, and readiness.\n🔍 Read the full briefing via the link in bio.\nㅤ\n\n#GlobalWealth #WealthStrategy #InvestmentMigration #GlobalMobility #CitizenshipByInvestment #ResidencyByInvestment #StKittsAndNevis #Panama #WealthDiversification #JurisdictionalStrategy #HNWIInvesting #FamilyOffice #AlternativeInvestments #GlobalCitizenSolutions #WealthPlanning #MultiJurisdictional #PassportPlanning",
